Week 2 — Phase 2: Security Planning & Performance Testing Methodology
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
PERFORMANCE TESTING PLAN (remote methodology)
How will you collect metrics remotely over SSH? What tools, how often, and what tables will you fill?
Tools planned: top/htop, free, vmstat, iostat, iotop, ss, ping, iperf3, ab, journalctl/logs
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
SECURITY CONFIGURATION CHECKLIST (plan)
□ SSH hardening (keys, disable password, no root login)
□ Firewall (allow SSH only from workstation IP)
□ MAC (AppArmor on Ubuntu / SELinux on Fedora)
□ Automatic security updates
□ fail2ban
□ User privilege management
□ Network isolation (host-only)
